Chocolate Layer Cake
Makes one, 9 inch, round, double layer cake.
10 minutes
10-13 minutes
55-58 miutes

3 c.- flour
2 c.- sugar
1/2 c.- 100% cocoa powder (dairy-free)
2 tsp- baking soda
1 tsp- salt
2 c.- water
2/3 c.- vegtable oil
2 tbsp- distilled white vinegar
2 tsp- vanilla extract
100% vegtable shortening

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Use 100% vegtable shortening to grease and then flour two 9 inch round cake pans.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar, and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon or wire whisk just until batter is smooth and al ingredients are well-blended.
Pour batter into prepared cake pans.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for about 35 minutes, or until center of cake is cooked.
Let cool completeley.
Frost.
